document_data.History:
Delphe's time as a Keeper started about a decade before {{yearlink|1375}}. In [[Midwinter]] of that year, she thwarted one new escape attempt by [[Carnis|the Traitor]]. Though Cynosure was of some help eventually on that day, she began to suspect the construct was not functioning properly.

Delphe confronted Telarian some days later after finding a letter from Captain [[Brathtar]], learning about the Epoch Chamber and the raid on a nearby wood elf encampment on the same day that the raid was taking place.{{cite book/Stardeep|150-155|13}} Considering the simultaneity implied the attackers were in league with the Traitor, she ordered the Causeway sealed, and disconnected all instances of Cynosure from the command functions in Stardeep.{{cite book/Stardeep|162-169|15}}

She agreed later to reinject Cynosure into the loop, instance by instance. However, Telarian left her to this task alone.{{cite book/Stardeep|187-189|17}} Due to fatigue, she decided to bring Cynosure back to functions with a small number of nodes, so that it could help her root out the infected nodes. Cynosure was able to inform her that the one subverting him was Telarian, and reveal the true extent of his subversions. She immediately sought him out, finding that he had ridden out of Stardeep through the Underdungeon;{{cite book/Stardeep|204-213|19}} When he returned with [[Kiril Duskmourn]], she tried to talk to her, and convince her that Telarian was the actual traitor. Before she could, Raidon Kane triggered a teleportation into The Well manually.{{cite book/Stardeep|276-282|27}}

Telarian's sword severed half her hand and sundered the Sign she carried.{{cite book/Stardeep|294-295|28}} After the battle, Delphe asked Raidon Kane to use his bonded Cerulean Sign to reinforce the wards around the Well.{{cite book/Stardeep|305-306|29}} He accepted.{{cite book/Stardeep|308-310|29}}

Per the construct [[Cynosure (construct)|Cynosure]], as of {{yearlink|1396}}, she had re-entered [[Sildëyuir]] fifteen years prior (placing the date in {{yearlink|1381}}) and never returned to Stardeep.{{cite book/Plague of Spells|161|12}}
